[2] Democratic Republic of Congo: measles decline
Date: Mon 21 Sep 2020
Source: Outbreak News Today [edited]
http://outbreaknewstoday.com/drc-measles-in-sustained-decline-dependent-on-continuing-vaccine-program-efforts-83405/


DRC measles in sustained decline, 'Dependent on continuing vaccine program efforts'
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The World Health Organization (WHO) reported today [21 Sep 2020] that the ongoing measles outbreak in Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC) is showing a sustained decline in new cases and deaths-reporting 245 suspected cases and 1 death during the week ending 6 Sep 2020.

WHO reminds while the declining trend in this long-standing measles outbreak is to be welcomed, this is dependent on continuing vaccine program efforts, without which cases will rebound.

Major infant vaccine programs have been ongoing in 2019 and 2020, with a total of 18.4 million children aged 6-59 months reached between October and December 2019.

From the start of the outbreak on 31 Dec 2018 to 6 Sep 2020, there has been a total of 382 370 cases and 7071 deaths (case fatality ratio 1.8%).

In 2020 to date, 70 899 suspected cases have been reported, including 1026 deaths (case fatality ratio 1.4%). This is a decrease compared to the same period in 2019, when there were 184 289 suspected cases and 3650 deaths reported.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from Google Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[This is wonderful news and a credit to the immunization program in the DRC. On 25 Aug 2020, the DRC declared the end of a 25-month outbreak of measles that claimed the lives of more than 7000 children under 5 years old. The outbreak was staunched by vaccination on a massive scale, in which millions of children and infants were immunized. This is especially noteworthy since COVID-19 makes it more difficult to maintain the program. - Mod.LK

HealthMap/ProMED map of DR Congo: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7806160,194]
